hed in yokohama in  the bank handled the first public loan in china in  thereafter issuing most public loans business developmentedit sir thomas jackson became chief manager in  during his twentysix year tenure the bank became a leader in asia notable events included being the first bank established in thailandcitation needed in  where it printed the countrys first banknotes acting as banker for the hong kong government from the s and participating in the management of british colonial government accounts in china japan penang and singapore a period of expansion followed with new buildings constructed in bangkok  manila  and shanghai  and a new head office building in hong kong in  second world waredit in anticipation of the japanese invasion of hong kong in  the banks head office moved to london during the period  the chief manager sir vandeleur grayburn and his successor david c edmondston both died while interned by the japanese arthur morse was appointed chief manager in  and led the bank after the war the head office moved back to hong kong in  during the japanese occupation the banks head office building was occupied as the headquarters of the hong kong japanese military government international expansionedit michael turner became chief manager in  and set about diversifying the business his tenure came to an end in  having established the hong kong and shanghai banking corporation of california  and having acquired the british bank of the middle east and the mercantile bank based in india in aug  turner was succeeded in  by jake saunders in  the chief managership was superseded as the top executive role in the bank by an executive chairmanship saunders took this role until retirement in  and was succeeded as chief manager in  by hj shen the managing director of maysun trading co and the former head of the central trust of china who became the first ethnic chinese to be appointed to the position of chief manager of the bank under saunders tenure the bank conti